radiographic_examinations.findings: Mixed signals in bilateral inguinal canal (considered vascular shadow). Uterus and ovaries were not visualized.
No cystic or solid mass in bilateral adrenal.
Hypoechoic mass (considered primordial uterus) in posterior bladder, and hypoechoic masses (considered bilateral testicles) in bilateral groin.
Bone age was in the normal range (12 years old).
